ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Intimate Interaction. If you wanted to talk to someone about the things that are very personal and private, who would you talk to? Number of people
Intimate Interaction. During the last month, how many of these people did you actually talk to about things that were personal and private
Intimate Interaction. How would you rate your satisfaction or dissatisfaction with the times you talked to people about your personal and private feelings during the past month
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Intimate Interaction. During the past month, how much do you think you needed people to talk to about things that were very personal and private
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Material aid. If you needed to borrow $25 or something valuable, who are the people you know who would loan or give you $25 or more, or would give you something (a physical object) that was valuable? Number of people
Material aid. During the past month, how many of these people actually loaned or gave you some money over $25 or gave or loaned you some valuable object that you needed?
Material aid. During the past month, how satisfied or dissatisfied were you with the things that people loaned or gave to you?
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Material aid. During the past month, how much you think you needed people who could loan or give you things that you needed?
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Advice. Who would you go to if a situation came up when you needed some advice? Number of people
Advice. During the past month, how many of these people actually gave you some important advice?
Advice. During the past month, how satisfied or dissatisfied were you with the advice that you were given?
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Advice. During the past month, how much you think you needed to get advice?
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Positive feedback. Who were the people who you could expect to let you know when they like your ideas or the things that you do?  They might be people you mentioned before or new people. Number of people
Positive feedback. During the past month, how many of these people actually let you know that they liked your ideas or the things that you did?
Positive feedback. During the past month, how satisfied or dissatisfied were you with the times that people told you that they liked your ideas or the things that you did?
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Positive feedback. During the past month, how much you think you needed to have people let you know when they liked your ideas or the things that you did?
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Physical assistance. Who are the people who you could call on to give up some of their time and energy to help to take care of something that you needed to do--things like driving you someplace you needed to go, helping you do some work around the house, going to the store for you, and things like that? Number of people
Physical assistance. During the past month how many of these people actually pitched in to help you do things that you needed some help with?
Physical assistance. During the past month, how satisfied or dissatisfied were you with the help you received in doing these things that you needed to do?
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Physical assistance. During the past month, how much did you feel you needed people who would pitch in to help you do things?
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Social participation. Who are the people who you could get together with to have fun or to relax? These could be new names or ones you've listed before. Number of people
Social participation. During the past month, how many of these people did you actually get together with to have fun or to relax?
Social participation. During the past month how satisfied or dissatisfied were you with the times that you got together with people just have fun and relax?
Notes: 1=very dissatisfied; 2= moderately dissatisfied; 3=slightly dissatisfied; 4=neither satisfied or dissatisfied; 5= slightly satisfied; 6=moderately satisfied; 7=very satisfied

ElementDescription: Social participation.How much do you think that you needed to get together with other people for fun and relaxation during the past month?
Notes: 1= no need at all; 2=slight need; 3=moderate need; 4=great need; 5=very great need

ElementDescription: Negative interactions. Who are the people who you can expect to have some unpleasant disagreements with or people who you can expect to make you angry and upset? Number of people
Negative interactions. During the past month, how many of these people actually had some unpleasant disagreements with you or actually made you angry and upset?

ElementDescription: Age of a person from network
Notes: 1=More than 2 years younger than child; 2= Child's age, plus or minus 2 years; 3=More than 2 years older than child; 4=Adult, over 18

ElementDescription: Where does the person from network live?
Notes: 1=In child's home; 2= Within walking distance; 3=Same city, but not within walking distance; 4=Different city

ElementDescription: How often do you usually see
Notes: 1=Daily, or almost daily, 5-7 days/week; 2=A few times a week, 1-4 days/week; 3=A few times per month, 1-3 days/month; 4=Less than once a month, 1-11 days/year; 5= Less than once per year

ElementDescription: When is the last time you saw
Notes: 1= Earlier today; 2= Within past week; 3= Within past month; 4= Within last six months; 5= Six-Twelve months ago; 6= More than a year ago

ElementDescription: How much would you say you care about that person
Notes: 0=Not at all; 1=A little; 2=Some; 3=A lot; 4=A Real lot

ElementDescription: How much do you think that person cares about you
Notes: 0=Not at all; 1=A little; 2=Some; 3=A lot; 4=A Real lot

ElementDescription: Type of support provided by the person mentioned
Notes: 1=Private Feelings; 2=Material Needs; 3=Shared Positive Experiences; 4= Social Participation; 5= Advice; 6=Nevative Contact; 999=Not Answered
